ook, try to stay focused on it the whole time that I am reading. One way to stay focused when you are reading is to ask questions. When you ask questions, you show curiosity about the book.**"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"curiosity"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Vocabulary Card."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_body-text","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Use Equity Sticks during reading to pick children to answer questions."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 4–5"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The mother kangaroo keeps her joey, which is the name for her baby, in a pouch. Why do you think she does that?"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 6–7"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"This mother transports her pup on her chest. Human parents often transport their children, too! They can transport their children in a car, on a bus, or on a bike! "}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_hilight_teacher_inst_new","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Revisit "},{"type":"element","name":"rac_highlight_teacher_inst_Italic","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"transports "}]},{"type":"text","text":"Vocabulary Card."}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"Why doesn’t the sea otter transport her pup in a car?"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"pages 12–13"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_teacher-talk_blue","elements":[{"type":"text","text":"The baby manatee swims close to its mother. Where does the baby like the most?"}]},{"type":"element","name":"rac_d-hed_page_number","elements":[{"type":"text","tex